bug.short_desc: [1.8] Parameter names for enum constructor not available

long_desc.thetext: I just wonder why the test does not fail for java.math.RoundingMode. Does it depend in JavaC vs EJC?

Enum constructors receive two synthetic arguments, that may have something to do with it, Assigning to Jesper tentatively as this may be the covered by JEP 118 and JEP 120 - to do with reflection retrieving method parameter names and their making it to the class file. Javac may already be implementing the JEPs (assuming they have a bearing)
Jesper, if this has no connection to the two Java 8 JEPs feel free to reset back to inbox.

Yes, this should be covered by the changes for JEP118, specifically bug 406973 for parsing the binary information, and bug 406982 which will generate them for e.g. enums. However, we should probably check for argument lengths, so we don't get 'BOOM', but 'arg0' and 'arg1' instead.

I think two things need to happen:
1. IMethodBinding should provide an API to retrieve the parameter names. 2. When the programmer is going through the model element, using: org.eclipse.jdt.internal.core.BinaryMethod.getParameterNames(), we should before going the javadoc route, should retrieve the parameters gathered (if gathered) from the new attribute.
Anirban, thanks for taking over this.
